ingredientsDesc:
Insstruction Leaflet: giving full assay details.
QC Certificate: indicating the expected performance of the batch
β2GP1 Coated Wells: 12breakpart 8 well strips coated with human β2GP1 antigen.
Type II Sample Diluent: 2 bottles containing 50 ml of buffer for sample dilution.
Wash Buffer (20x Concentrate): 1 bottle containing 50 ml of a 20-fold concentrated buffer for washing the wells.
β2GP1 IgM Calibrators: 5 bottles each containing 1.2 ml of diluted human serum, with the following concentrations of anti-β2GP1 autoantibody: 300, 100, 33.3, 11.1, 3.7 U/ml.
β2GP1 IgM Positive Control: 1 bottle containing 1.2 ml of diluted human serum. The expected value is given on the QC certificate.
β2GP1 Negative Control: 1 bottle containing 1.2 ml of diluted human serum. The expected value is given on the QC certificate.
β2GP1 IgM Conjugate: 1 bottle containing 12 ml of purified peroxidase labeled antibody.
TMB Substrate: 1 bottle containing 14 ml TMB substrate.
Stop Solution: 1 bottle containing 14 ml of 3M phosp
